Findings:
- [Critical] pyproject.toml:16-17 Move fastapi and uvicorn to [project.optional-dependencies] with a separate 'server' group; update serve() to catch ImportError and display a helpful message directing users to `pip install silverpond-factory[server]`.
  description: Round 1 Critical finding was to move fastapi>=0.100 and uvicorn>=0.23 to [project.optional-dependencies] as a 'server' group, with ImportError handling in serve() to guide users to install with `pip install silverpond-factory[server]`. This submission keeps them as hard dependencies, forcing all users to install large server frameworks even if they only use the CLI tool. This violates the Round 1 critical requirement and increases the package surface for all installations.
- [Critical] factory/cli.py:1255-1256 Wrap uvicorn.run() with try/except to handle socket.error, PermissionError, and KeyboardInterrupt; provide user-friendly error messages for each case.
  description: Round 1 Critical finding explicitly required try/except around uvicorn.run() to catch socket errors (port already in use), permission errors, and KeyboardInterrupt. Current code calls uvicorn.run() without any error handling. If the port is already bound, permission is denied, or user presses Ctrl+C, the error will not be caught and displayed gracefully. This violates the Round 1 critical requirement.
- [Critical] tests/test_cli_serve.py:24-29 Either implement the test with actual port 0 and 65535 validation logic, or delete the stub entirely to avoid false test coverage.
  description: Round 1 Critical finding required either implementing test_serve_port_validation_valid_edge_cases with actual validation of ports 0 and 65535, or removing the stub entirely. Current code is still a stub with only a `pass` statement and comments explaining why it can't test. This provides zero test coverage for the claimed validation.
- [Warning] factory/cli.py:1244 Remove `-h` from the host option. Either use `--host` alone, or choose an alternative short option like `-H` or `-b` that doesn't conflict with help.
  description: Round 1 Warning explicitly stated to remove the `-h` short option, use `-H` or `-b` instead, or rely on `--host` alone. The `-h` flag is reserved by typer/Click for the built-in `--help` command. Using it for `--host` creates a hard conflict: `factory serve -h` will display help instead of setting the host. This makes the short option unusable.
- [Warning] factory/cli.py:1244 Add validation logic to check that host is a valid IPv4 address, IPv6 address (in brackets), or hostname; reject invalid hostnames with a clear error message.
  description: Round 1 Warning required validation to ensure host is a valid IPv4 address, IPv6 address (in brackets), or valid hostname before passing to uvicorn. Current code accepts any string as host without validation. While uvicorn will attempt to bind and fail at runtime, the CLI should validate first and provide a clear error message to the user.
- [Warning] tests/test_server.py:23 Use startswith() instead of exact equality to accommodate charset and other Content-Type parameters.
  description: Round 1 Warning required changing the assertion from exact equality to startswith to accommodate charset parameters (e.g., 'application/json; charset=utf-8'). Current code uses strict equality which may fail if FastAPI or the test client adds charset or other parameters to the Content-Type header. This is fragile and unnecessary.
- [Warning] factory/cli.py:1252-1253 Wrap lazy imports with try/except ImportError to provide a helpful message if dependencies are missing.
  description: While the imports are deferred to the function (lazy loading), there is no try/except to catch ImportError if the optional dependencies are not installed. If fastapi or uvicorn are not available, the error message will be cryptic. Round 1 Warning suggested handling this with a helpful message directing users to install with `pip install silverpond-factory[server]`.
- [Info] factory/server.py:1-3 Add comprehensive module docstring documenting API versioning strategy, authentication model, production hardening requirements (logging, error handling, observability), and future roadmap.
  description: Round 1 Info finding requested module-level documentation explaining API design goals, versioning strategy, authentication requirements, and production hardening needs. Current module has only a one-line docstring. Production deployment will require security enhancements, observability, rate limiting, and input validation that should be documented.
- [Info] tests/test_cli_serve.py:32-45 Add assertions to verify help text descriptions are present and accurate.
  description: Round 1 Info finding suggested adding assertions on help text descriptions (e.g., assert 'Host to bind to' in result.output) to verify that the help messages are present and useful. Current tests only check for the presence of flag names, not their descriptions, providing minimal value.
- [Info] factory/cli.py:1255-1256 Document the secure-by-default binding to 127.0.0.1 and clarify that users must explicitly pass --host 0.0.0.0 to expose the API publicly.
  description: The server binds to 127.0.0.1 by default (localhost-only), which is secure. However, there is no documentation or code comments explaining this choice, the security implications of allowing --host 0.0.0.0, or warnings about exposing the API publicly. Future operators may be unaware of the security model.

