ation/json\")` in test_server.py:23\n   - Now handles charset parameters (e.g., \"application/json; charset=utf-8\") across FastAPI versions\n\n### Info Issues Fixed\n\n7. **Finding #1 (Info): Missing API Documentation**\n   - Expanded `factory/server.py` module docstring with:\n     - API design philosophy (versioning strategy, future v1 prefix)\n     - Authentication requirements placeholder\n     - Organization pattern (APIRouter for endpoint groups)\n     - Production roadmap (health checks, logging, metrics, auth, tracing)\n\n8. **Finding #7 (Info): Minimal Endpoint Lacks Logging**\n   - Added `import logging` and logger setup in factory/server.py\n   - Added `logger.info()` call in /hello endpoint\n   - Foundation for production observability\n\n9. **Finding #3 (Info): Help Text Tests**\n   - Enhanced both `test_serve_accepts_host_option()` and `test_serve_accepts_port_option()`\n   - Now assert help descriptions are present: \"Host to bind to\" and \"Port to bind to\"\n   - Tests are no longer shallow smoke tests\n\n### Additional Improvements\n\n- Added `tests/__init__.py` package marker\n- All imports properly organized and error-handled\n- Test coverage now includes edge cases, validation, and help text verification\n- Installation via optional-dependencies reduces supply chain risk and package size for CLI-only users\n\n### Installation Notes\n\n```bash\n# For CLI-only use (no server)\npip install silverpond-factory\n\n# For server feature\npip install silverpond-factory[server]\n\n# For development with tests\npip install silverpond-factory[server,test]\n```",
    "unified_diff": "diff --git a/factory/cli.py b/factory/cli.py\nindex 59d1509..9d8f34e 100644\n--- a/factory/cli.py\n+++ b/factory/cli.py\n@@ -1237,6 +1237,50 @@ def slack_listen(\n         sm_client.close()\n \n \n+# ── serve ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n+\n+@app.command()\n+def serve(\n+    host: str = typer.Option(\"127.0.0.1\", \"--host\", \"-h\", help=\"Host to bind to\"),\n+    port: int = typer.Option(8000, \"--port\", \"-p\", help=\"Port to bind to\"),\n+) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Start the FastAPI server with the hello endpoint.\"\"\"\n+    import socket\n+    from ipaddress import ip_address, AddressValueError\n+\n+    # Validate port range\n+    if port < 0 or port > 65535:\n+        typer.echo(f\"Port must be between 0 and 65535, got {port}\", err=True)\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    # Validate host\n+    try:\n+        socket.inet_aton(host) if ':' not in host else socket.inet_pton(socket.AF_INET6, host)\n+    except (socket.error, OSError):\n+        # Try as hostname\n+        try:\n+            socket.getaddrinfo(host, port, 0, socket.SOCK_STREAM)\n+        except socket.gaierror:\n+            typer.echo(f\"Invalid host address: {host}\", err=True)\n+            raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    try:\n+        from factory.server import app as server_app\n+        import uvicorn\n+    except ImportError:\n+        typer.echo(\n+            \"FastAPI server dependencies not installed. \"\n+            \"Install with: pip install silverpond-factory[server]\",\n+            err=True,\n+        )\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    try:\n+        console.print(f\"Starting server on http://{host}:{port}\")\n+        uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port)\n+    except (OSError, PermissionError) as e:\n+        typer.echo(f\"Failed to start server: {e}\", err=True)\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n+        console.print(\"\\nServer stopped.\")\n+        raise typer.Exit(0)\n+\n \n # ── entry point ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n \ndiff --git a/factory/server.py b/factory/server.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..c848b47\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/factory/server.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+\"\"\"FastAPI server for Silverpond Factory.\n+\n+API Design:\n+    - Versioning: Currently v1 (no prefix required for MVP endpoints)\n+    - Future endpoints will use /api/v1/ prefix for proper versioning\n+    - Authentication: Not yet implemented; consider OAuth2/JWT for production\n+    - Organization: Use APIRouter for endpoint groups as the API grows\n+    - Error handling: All endpoints should return standardized error responses\n+\n+Production Roadmap:\n+    - Add request/response logging for observability\n+    - Implement health check endpoint (/health)\n+    - Add metrics/monitoring hooks\n+    - Implement proper authentication and authorization\n+    - Add distributed tracing support\n+\"\"\"\n+import logging\n+from fastapi import FastAPI\n+\n+logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+app = FastAPI()\n+\n+\n+@app.get(\"/hello\")\n+def hello():\n+    \"\"\"Simple hello endpoint that returns a JSON response.\"\"\"\n+    logger.info(\"GET /hello endpoint called\")\n+    return {\"message\": \"Hello, World!\"}\ndiff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 23b4060..04ba2b7 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -13,6 +13,16 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"pyyaml>=6\",\n     \"questionary>=2\",\n     \"slack-sdk>=3.19\",\n ]\n \n+[project.optional-dependencies]\n+server = [\n+    \"fastapi>=0.100\",\n+    \"uvicorn>=0.23\",\n+]\n+test = [\n+    \"pytest>=7\",\n+    \"httpx>=0.24\",\n+]\n+\n [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\ndiff --git a/tests/__init__.py b/tests/__init__.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..964eec9\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/__init__.py\n@@ -0,0 +1 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for Silverpond Factory.\"\"\"\ndiff --git a/tests/test_cli_serve.py b/tests/test_cli_serve.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..3d4e2d8\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_cli_serve.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,70 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for the serve CLI command.\"\"\"\n+import pytest\n+from unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\n+from typer.testing import CliRunner\n+from factory.cli import app\n+\n+\n+runner = CliRunner()\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_port_validation_negative():\n+    \"\"\"Test that negative ports are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"-1\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Port must be between 0 and 65535\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_port_validation_too_high():\n+    \"\"\"Test that ports > 65535 are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"65536\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Port must be between 0 and 65535\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+@patch(\"factory.cli.uvicorn.run\")\ndef test_serve_port_validation_valid_edge_cases(mock_uvicorn):\n+    \"\"\"Test that valid edge cases (0 and 65535) pass validation.\"\"\"\n+    # Test port 0 (let OS choose available port)\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"0\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 0\n+    mock_uvicorn.assert_called_once()\n+    call_kwargs = mock_uvicorn.call_args[1]\n+    assert call_kwargs[\"port\"] == 0\n+\n+    # Reset mock\n+    mock_uvicorn.reset_mock()\n+\n+    # Test port 65535 (highest valid port)\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"65535\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 0\n+    mock_uvicorn.assert_called_once()\n+    call_kwargs = mock_uvicorn.call_args[1]\n+    assert call_kwargs[\"port\"] == 65535\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_host_validation_invalid():\n+    \"\"\"Test that invalid host addresses are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--host\", \"invalid..host\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Invalid host address\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+@patch(\"factory.cli.uvicorn.run\")\n+def test_serve_host_