  description: When user presses Ctrl+C (KeyboardInterrupt), the code exits with code 0 (success) and prints 'Server stopped.' Most CLI tools exit with code 130 (128 + SIGINT) or code 1 when interrupted. Exiting with 0 may confuse automation/scripts that expect a non-zero exit code on abnormal termination.
- [Info] pyproject.toml:18-23 Document the optional-dependency groups in README or CLAUDE.md with usage examples (pip install silverpond-factory[server,test], etc.)
  description: Current structure has `server` and `test` groups. As the project grows, consider adding documented groups like `dev` (includes both server and test), or `all` (includes everything). This improves discoverability and user experience.

