    "explanation": "## Summary of Auto-Fix\n\nThis unified diff addresses all 9 agreed-upon findings from the 2-round crucible review:\n\n### Critical Issues Fixed\n\n1. **Optional Dependencies (pyproject.toml)**: Moved `fastapi>=0.100` and `uvicorn>=0.23` from main `dependencies` to new `[project.optional-dependencies]` section under `server` group. Users now install with `pip install silverpond-factory[server]` for server feature.\n\n2. **Error Handling (factory/cli.py)**: Wrapped `uvicorn.run()` with comprehensive try/except:\n   - Catches `OSError` with errno-based detection (`errno.EADDRINUSE`, `errno.EACCES`) instead of fragile string matching\n   - Catches `KeyboardInterrupt` and exits with code 130 (standard SIGINT)\n   - Provides user-friendly error messages for each failure mode\n\n3. **Host Validation (factory/cli.py)**: Added `socket.getaddrinfo()` validation to reject invalid hostnames/IPs before attempting to bind. Invalid hosts exit with code 1 and clear error message.\n\n4. **Short Option Conflict (factory/cli.py)**: Changed host short option from `-h` (conflicts with help) to `-H`.\n\n5. **Test Implementation (tests/test_cli_serve.py)**: Implemented `test_serve_port_validation_valid_edge_cases()` with proper mocking of `uvicorn.run()`, testing that ports 0 and 65535 pass validation and reach uvicorn.\n\n### Warning Issues Fixed\n\n6. **Content-Type Assertion (tests/test_server.py)**: Changed exact equality `==` to `.startswith()` to accommodate charset parameters (e.g., \"application/json; charset=utf-8\") across FastAPI versions.\n\n7. **Help Text Tests (tests/test_cli_serve.py)**: Enhanced help text assertions to verify descriptions are present (\"Host to bind to\", \"Port to bind to\"), not just flag names.\n\n### Info Issues Fixed\n\n8. **API Documentation (factory/server.py)**: Expanded module docstring with:\n   - Versioning strategy (/api/v1/ for future)\n   - Router organization pattern\n   - Authentication requirements\n   - Production roadmap (logging, health checks, metrics, rate limiting, auth)\n\n9. **Endpoint Logging (factory/server.py)**: Added `import logging` and logger setup. `/hello` endpoint now logs `logger.info()` on invocation for observability foundation.\n\n### Installation Guide\n```bash\npip install silverpond-factory          # CLI only (no server)\npip install silverpond-factory[server]  # CLI + HTTP server\npip install silverpond-factory[test]    # Testing (pytest, httpx)\n```\n\n### Error Handling Examples\n- Port already in use: Clear message directing user to try different port\n- Permission denied: Explains ports <1024 require admin privileges  \n- Invalid host: Shows what host was rejected\n- Ctrl+C: Graceful shutdown with exit code 130 (standard SIGINT)",
    "unified_diff": "diff --git a/factory/cli.py b/factory/cli.py\nindex 59d1509..5a7c8e2 100644\n--- a/factory/cli.py\n+++ b/factory/cli.py\n@@ -1238,6 +1238,63 @@ def slack_listen(\n         sm_client.close()\n \n \n+# ── serve ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n+\n+@app.command()\n+def serve(\n+    host: str = typer.Option(\"127.0.0.1\", \"--host\", \"-H\", help=\"Host to bind to\"),\n+    port: int = typer.Option(8000, \"--port\", \"-p\", help=\"Port to bind to\"),\n+) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Start the FastAPI server with the hello endpoint.\"\"\"\n+    import socket\n+    import errno\n+\n+    # Validate port range\n+    if port < 0 or port > 65535:\n+        typer.echo(f\"Port must be between 0 and 65535, got {port}\", err=True)\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    # Validate host (IPv4, IPv6, or hostname)\n+    try:\n+        socket.getaddrinfo(host, port, 0, socket.SOCK_STREAM)\n+    except socket.gaierror:\n+        typer.echo(f\"Invalid host address: {host}\", err=True)\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    # Import optional dependencies\n+    try:\n+        from factory.server import app as server_app\n+        import uvicorn\n+    except ImportError:\n+        typer.echo(\n+            \"FastAPI server dependencies not installed. \"\n+            \"Install with: pip install silverpond-factory[server]\",\n+            err=True,\n+        )\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+\n+    console.print(f\"Starting server on http://{host}:{port}\")\n+    try:\n+        uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port)\n+    except OSError as e:\n+        if e.errno == errno.EADDRINUSE:\n+            typer.echo(\n+                f\"Port {port} is already in use. Try a different port with --port.\",\n+                err=True,\n+            )\n+        elif e.errno == errno.EACCES:\n+            typer.echo(\n+                f\"Permission denied binding to {host}:{port}. \"\n+                f\"Ports below 1024 require administrative privileges.\",\n+                err=True,\n+            )\n+        else:\n+            typer.echo(f\"Failed to start server: {e}\", err=True)\n+        raise typer.Exit(1)\n+    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n+        console.print(\"\\nServer stopped.\")\n+        raise typer.Exit(130)  # Standard SIGINT exit code\n+\n \n # ── entry point ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n \ndiff --git a/factory/server.py b/factory/server.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..b4a2f51\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/factory/server.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+\"\"\"FastAPI server for Silverpond Factory.\n+\n+API Design:\n+    - Versioning: Currently v1 (no prefix required for MVP endpoints).\n+    - Future endpoints will use /api/v1/ prefix for proper semantic versioning.\n+    - Organization: Use APIRouter for endpoint groups as the API grows.\n+    - Authentication: Not yet implemented; consider OAuth2/JWT for production.\n+\n+Production Roadmap:\n+    - Add request/response logging and structured tracing.\n+    - Implement health check endpoint (/health).\n+    - Add metrics and monitoring hooks (Prometheus, OpenTelemetry).\n+    - Implement proper authentication and authorization layers.\n+    - Add rate limiting and request validation.\n+    - Document API contract and maintain backward compatibility.\n+\"\"\"\n+import logging\n+from fastapi import FastAPI\n+\n+logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+app = FastAPI()\n+\n+\n+@app.get(\"/hello\")\n+def hello():\n+    \"\"\"Simple hello endpoint that returns a JSON response.\n+\n+    Returns:\n+        dict: A JSON object with a greeting message.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    logger.info(\"GET /hello endpoint called\")\n+    return {\"message\": \"Hello, World!\"}\ndiff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 5ab57d5..27ce0e9 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -17,6 +17,16 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"slack-sdk>=3.19\",\n ]\n \n+[project.optional-dependencies]\n+server = [\n+    \"fastapi>=0.100\",\n+    \"uvicorn>=0.23\",\n+]\n+test = [\n+    \"pytest>=7\",\n+    \"httpx>=0.24\",\n+]\n+\n [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n \ndiff --git a/tests/__init__.py b/tests/__init__.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..964eec9\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/__init__.py\n@@ -0,0 +1 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for Silverpond Factory.\"\"\"\ndiff --git a/tests/test_cli_serve.py b/tests/test_cli_serve.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..a3b8c45\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_cli_serve.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,75 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for the serve CLI command.\"\"\"\n+import pytest\n+from unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\n+from typer.testing import CliRunner\n+from factory.cli import app\n+\n+\n+runner = CliRunner()\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_port_validation_negative():\n+    \"\"\"Test that negative ports are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"-1\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Port must be between 0 and 65535\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_port_validation_too_high():\n+    \"\"\"Test that ports > 65535 are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"65536\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Port must be between 0 and 65535\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+@patch(\"factory.cli.uvicorn.run\")\n+def test_serve_port_validation_valid_edge_cases(mock_uvicorn):\n+    \"\"\"Test that valid edge cases (0 and 65535) pass validation.\"\"\"\n+    # Test port 0 (let OS choose available port)\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"0\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 0\n+    assert mock_uvicorn.called\n+    call_kwargs = mock_uvicorn.call_args[1]\n+    assert call_kwargs[\"port\"] == 0\n+\n+    # Reset mock\n+    mock_uvicorn.reset_mock()\n+\n+    # Test port 65535 (highest valid port)\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--port\", \"65535\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 0\n+    assert mock_uvicorn.called\n+    call_kwargs = mock_uvicorn.call_args[1]\n+    assert call_kwargs[\"port\"] == 65535\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_host_validation_invalid():\n+    \"\"\"Test that invalid host addresses are rejected.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--host\", \"invalid..host\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 1\n+    assert \"Invalid host address\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+@patch(\"factory.cli.uvicorn.run\")\n+def test_serve_host_validation_valid_ipv4(mock_uvicorn):\n+    \"\"\"Test that valid IPv4 addresses are accepted.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--host\", \"192.168.1.1\"])\n+    assert result.exit_code == 0\n+    assert mock_uvicorn.called\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_accepts_host_option():\n+    \"\"\"Test that the serve command accepts --host option with correct help text.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--help\"])\n+    assert \"--host\" in result.output\n+    assert \"-H\" in result.output\n+    assert \"Host to bind to\" in result.output\n+\n+\n+def test_serve_accepts_port_option():\n+    \"\"\"Test that the serve command accepts --port option with correct help text.\"\"\"\n+    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"serve\", \"--help\"])\n+    assert \"--port\" in result.output\n+    assert \"-p\" in result.output\n+    assert \"Port to bind to\" in result.output\ndiff --git a/tests/test_server.py b/tests/test_server.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..ebb1f28\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_server.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for the FastAPI server.\"\"\"\n+import pytest\n+from fastapi.testclient import TestClient\n+from factory.server import app\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def client():\n+    \"\"\"Fixture for FastAPI test client.\"\"\"\n+    return TestClient(app)\n+\n+\n+def test_hello_endpoint_returns_json(client):\n+    \"\"\"Test that the /hello endpoint returns a JSON response.\"\"\"\n+    response = client.get(\"/hello\")\n+    assert response.status_code == 200\n+    assert response.json() == {\"message\": \"Hello, World!\"}\n+\n+\n+def test_hello_endpoint_content_type(client):\n+    \"\"\"Test that the /hello endpoint returns the correct content type.\"\"\"\n+    response = client.get(\"/hello\")\n+    assert response.headers[\"content-type\"].startswith(\"application/json\")\n+\n+\n+def test_hello_endpoint_method_validation(client):\n+    \"\"\"Test that the /hello endpoint only accepts GET requests.\"\"\"\n+    assert client.post(\"/hello\").status_code == 405\n+    assert client.put(\"/hello\").status_code == 405\n+    assert client.delete(\"/hello\").status_code == 405\n+\n+\n+def test_hello_endpoint_404(client):\n+    \"\"\"Test that non-existent endpoints return 404.\"\"\"\n+    response = client.get(\"/nonexistent\")\n+    assert response.status_code == 404\n"
